The paper deals with the problem of stable matchings, which is a well-studied topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it deals with matching preferences of two sets of agents. The algorithm proposed in the paper is a heuristic approach, which involves making decisions based on certain criteria, and hence falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) as it deals with finding the best possible matching under certain constraints. Finally, the paper proposes a faster and simpler algorithm, which involves optimization of computational resources, and hence falls under the category of computational complexity and optimization (cs.SI).
